X-Career-User database migrations.

Migration files live under `src/infra/db/migrations`; `alembic.ini` resolves
this path from the repository root, so Alembic commands can be run from any
working directory when `-c` points to the repository config.

Load all database connection settings, including the target schema, from an
untracked environment file or an approved secret manager. Do not place real
environment names or credentials in this repository.

Run migrations from the repository root:

    alembic upgrade head

For automation, inject the same settings through the CI/CD secret store before
running the command.

The Alembic version table is stored in the target schema as
`alembic_version_user`.
